main event: A bright light was spotted moving erratically in the sky near Moses Lake, Washington on August 6, 1964.
interesting points: The object was first seen stationary in the southwest sky, then it began moving in an erratic pattern, up, down, and sideways, for approximately fifteen minutes before disappearing.
An aerial search of the area was conducted, but no further sightings of the object were reported.
Ground exploration of the site revealed an apparent ground disturbance, which was photographed and included with the report.
Project Blue Book investigators were unable to conclusively identify the nature of the reported UFO, and the case remains classified as 'unidentified'.

A separate incident involved a silver, round object approximately 40 feet in diameter that hovered in the air for several minutes before flying away at a high rate of speed. This was also investigated but classified as a case of 'mistaken identity' by the Project Blue Book consultant.
sighted object: bright light, circular object approximately 30-40 feet in diameter
photographs: yes, the report includes photographs of the ground disturbance and the aerial terrain
